title Debug Service Logging Flow

|initgui|
start
:Boot initgui.js;
:Instantiate DebugService;
:register('debug', new DebugService())
→ add to service registry;

|DebugService|
:Service framework invokes _init();
:Initialize this.enabled_logs = [] (empty array);

|ExecService|
:DebugService retrieves ExecService
via services.get('exec');

|DebugService|
:Register param provider callback
on ExecService instance;
note right
  Callback fires whenever ExecService
  needs query params for process launch
end note

|initgui|
:Service initialization complete;

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' Param Provider Callback (triggered later)
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

|ExecService|
:ExecService triggers param provider
callback before launching a process;

|DebugService|
if (enabled_logs.length > 0?) then (yes)
  :Return { enabled_logs: enabled_logs.join('&#59;') };
  note right: Semicolon-separated\ncategory list
else (no)
  :Return {} (empty params);
endif

|ExecService|
:Merge params into process launch query string;

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' logs(category) — Enable Log Category
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

|initgui|
:Consumer calls DebugService.logs(category);

|DebugService|
:Build postMessage payload
{ $: 'puterjs-debug', cmd: 'log.on', category };
:Push category into this.enabled_logs[];

fork
  |DebugService|
  :Call puter.logger.on(category);
  |puter.logger|
  :Enable log category in
  global Puter SDK logger;

fork again
  |DebugService|
  :Query all iframes via
  jQuery $('iframe').each(fn);
  :Iterate over each iframe in DOM;

  |iframes|
  repeat
    :Receive iframe reference;
    :iframe.contentWindow
    .postMessage(payload, '*');
    :Child frame enables log category;
  repeat while (more iframes?) is (yes)
  ->no;

end fork

|DebugService|
:logs() completes
(no return value — side-effects only);

stop

@enduml
